## Description
Add agent-specific permission configuration to `BeadsService.processConfig()` to enable the question tool for beads-planner-agent.

## Background
Plugin agents defined in markdown don't automatically apply frontmatter permissions. We need to set them programmatically in the plugin's config hook, just like we already do for bash permissions.

## Instructions
1. Open `src/service/beads-service.ts`
2. Find the `processConfig()` method (around line 112)
3. After setting `config.default_agent = "beads-planner-agent"` (line 118), add agent permission configuration:

```typescript
// Set default agent to beads-planner-agent when beads is active
config.default_agent = "beads-planner-agent";

// Configure beads-planner-agent permissions
if (!config.agent) {
  config.agent = {};
}
if (!config.agent["beads-planner-agent"]) {
  config.agent["beads-planner-agent"] = {};
}
if (!config.agent["beads-planner-agent"].permission) {
  config.agent["beads-planner-agent"].permission = {};
}

// Enable question tool (for structured user questions during planning)
config.agent["beads-planner-agent"].permission.question = "allow";

// Enforce read-only mode for code (deny all edit operations)
if (!config.agent["beads-planner-agent"].permission.edit) {
  config.agent["beads-planner-agent"].permission.edit = {};
}
config.agent["beads-planner-agent"].permission.edit["*"] = "deny";
```

4. This should be placed right after line 118, before the auto_approve_beads check

