## Description
Design a custom OpenCode tool that provides runtime system information about the opencode-coder plugin. This tool will be callable by Claude and skills.

## Tool Architecture

### Location
`.opencode/tools/system-info.ts`

### Tool Name
`system_info` (filename becomes tool name)

### Purpose
Provide real-time system information about:
- Plugin version and status
- OpenCode version and config
- Beads integration status
- GitHub integration status
- Git repository status
- Health checks
- Knowledge base stats

### How Skills Will Use It

```markdown
---
name: using-coder-plugin
description: Guide with live system checks
---

# Using OpenCode Coder Plugin

## Current System Status

<use system_info tool to get current status>

Based on the system info:
- Plugin version: {plugin.version}
- Beads: {integrations.beads.enabled}
...
```

## Tool Interface

### Input (Args)
```typescript
{
  // No arguments needed for basic call
  // Or optional args for specific sections:
  sections?: string[] // e.g., ["plugin", "beads", "github"]
}
```

### Output (Return Value)
```typescript
